SPLIT ACES tracked the early pace while three wide and between runners, lost ground on the turn while two wide, dropped back into the stretch and gave way. PER THE HORSERACING INTEGRITY AND WELFARE UNIT, ONE LITTLE INDIAN HAS BEEN DQ'D FOR A POSITIVE TEST.

SGT POWELL was sent after an alert beginning, was engaged by G'S LAST CHANCE in the early stages and contested a solid pace with that rival, disputed decent fractions while clear of the others through the backstretch run, came back to the field along the far turn, shook free of G'S LAST CHANCE into upper stretch, battled with BIG BENO to the furlong marker, could not muster a response in deep stretch and tired in the late stages. G'S LAST CHANCE was prominent leaving the start, engaged with SGT POWELL into the first turn and contested the pace with that rival into the backstretch run, disputed the decent pace with SGT POWELL to the half-mile pole, continued to duel into the far turn, lost position into the stretch, chased to the furlong marker and gave way in the final sixteenth.
